
At the moment these are the list of things to do in the MC Rewrite project.

For bug tracking, please write to:

	https://github.com/Andres2626/Minecraft-Rewrite/issues
	
or

	minecraftrewrite21@gmail.com
	
To mark one of these items as 'DONE' and once changes have been made 
to the project, submit a pull request to:

	https://github.com/Andres2626/Minecraft-Rewrite/pulls

===============================================================================

## Game
    - [ ] Separate some parts of the game into a separate library.
    - [ ] Move fog effect to postfx shader.
    - [ ] Improve rendering process.
## Build
    - [ ] Compiler warnings.
    - [x] C4251 warning (exporting classes with DLL members) in MSVC.
    - [ ] Compiler detection (core/common.h)
        - [x] MSVC.
        - [x] GNU.
        - [ ] Other compilers.
    - [ ] Stabilize ABI.
## Engine
    - [ ] Some Application functions are not used by engine (stop and suspended)
    - [ ] Improve finish process
## Directories
    - [ ] Separate dependencies and third-party libraries.
    - [ ] Create third-party directory
## Modding System
    - [ ] Dynamic Loading (DL) — low-level modding system.
    - [ ] Dynamic Loading protocol (dlfcn.h on Unix/LoadLibrary on Windows).
    - [ ] The code in the `dl/` folder is not yet used.
    - [ ] Lua scripting — high-level modding system.
    - [ ] Hybrid system: DL + Lua.
## Platform Support
    - [ ] Windows (older versions, from Windows 2000).
    - [ ] Linux (untested).
    - [ ] Web (via Emscripten)
    - [ ] Android (high priority).
    - [ ] Apple (macOS/iOS).
    - [ ] Xbox.
    - [ ] Wii.
## Graphics Support
    - [ ] OpenGL ES.
    - [ ] WebGL (via Emscripten).
    - [ ] DirectX.
    - [ ] Vulkan.
## Architecture / Engine
    - [ ] Separate the engine from the main project.
    - [ ] Create an independent and reusable game engine.
    - [ ] Implement an event subsystem from scratch.
    - [ ] Support for geometry shaders.
    - [ ] Implement ShaderManager.
    - [ ] Generate zombie mesh with MeshFactory.
## Tools and Utilities
    - [ ] Implement an argument parser in the engine (getopt).
    - [ ] Cross-compilation support.
## Performance
    - [ ] High performace and stability in main game.
          - [ ] Implement batching for Renderer2D.
          - [ ] Implement instancing for zombie entities.
          - [ ] Implement Binary Greedy Meshing generation.
    - [ ] Implement the FPS limit in the Application class.
## Documentation
